## Troubleshooting

### Docker keychain error
If Docker commands fail with "keychain cannot be accessed", the macOS keychain is locked. Unlock it:
```bash
ssh macmini 'security unlock-keychain -p "<password>" ~/Library/Keychains/login.keychain-db'
```
Auto-lock is disabled via `security set-keychain-settings`, but a reboot may re-lock it.

### Port 8000 conflict
Both sim4action (Python, IPv4) and Docker backend (IPv6) listen on port 8000. This coexistence works because they bind to different address families. Do NOT change Docker's backend port mapping without checking sim4action first.

### Nginx won't reload
The master process runs as root. Passwordless sudo is configured for `/opt/homebrew/bin/nginx` and `/bin/kill` via `/etc/sudoers.d/nginx-reload`.
